    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** lineup for April 17 is headlined by **Kyle Tucker**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 85.90. His matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano is exceptionally favorable, buoyed by a 14% park factor boost and the benefits of leading off, which maximizes his exposure to high-leverage opportunities. Alongside him, **Andy Pages** (74.37) and **Gunnar Henderson** (78.15) provide the offensive backbone today. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from a 14% dynamic platoon edge, while **Andy Pages** finds himself in an ideal hitting environment that elevates his raw projection. **Drake Baldwin** also warrants attention as a high-upside play (71.16) due to an exploitable matchup against Taijuan Walker, where his strong projected order position (#2) and SP skill advantage create a robust scoring profile.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involves the exclusion of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.57), who sits just outside our optimal starting configuration. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** possesses an elite xwOBA of .384, his matchup against Michael Soroka is statistically inferior to those of our starters, particularly when accounting for the negative platoon impact and the overall projected efficiency of our outfield trio. We are prioritizing speed and dynamic platoon advantages elsewhere, leaving high-floor contributors like **Nolan Schanuel** (58.93) and **Heliot Ramos** (55.89) in the lineup to balance the roster. Note that all scores are currently based on \"Lineup Pending\" status; should official lineups shuffle our hitters into lower-value spots, we may see a decline in the real-time efficiency of players like **Liam Hicks**, whose current status below the 40-point floor warrants close monitoring to avoid unnecessary usage of our game caps.",
